				<h1>BIS Quarterly Review, September 2023</h1>

				


				
 
  
   
    
     
      
      
       <img src="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/czQwkhJtxQB2E4mkKnfMQkhqZruKbeW0AIiM0-tG97I=/aHR0cDovL3d3dy5iaXMub3JnL2ltZy9wb2RjYXN0cy9xdDIzMDkuanBn" loading="lazy"/>
       
      
     
     
     <p> Media briefing on the BIS Quarterly Review, September 2023 (00:35:42) 
     </p> 
      
      <p> by <a href="http://www.bis.org/author/claudio_borio.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Claudio Borio</a> and <a href="http://www.bis.org/author/hyun_song_shin.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Hyun Song Shin</a> </p> 
      
     <p>  18 Sep 2023  BIS Quarterly Review, September 2023 
     </p> 
     
    
    
     
     <p>Claudio Borio and Hyun Song Shin summarise the September 2023 Quarterly Review and answer journalists&#39; questions about financial market developments and the economic outlook.</p> 
     
    
    
     
     <audio controls=""> 
      <source src="https://traffic.libsyn.com/secure/bispodcast/BIS_Quarterly_Review_September_2023_podcast_final.mp3"/> 
     </audio> 
     
    
   
  
				

					
	
			<h3 id="overview">Overview</h3>

				
					
						
								<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309a.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Resilient risk-taking in financial markets</a>
							<p>
							</p>
						
					
					
						<p><em>With the end of the interest rate hiking phase in sight, investors focused on macroeconomic developments and their policy implications.</em></p> <a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309a.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">More...</a>
					
				
	
	
			<h3 id="specialfeatures">Special features</h3>

				
					
						
							
										
											<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309b.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
											<p></p>
											</a>
										
								
									
										<p>
												<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309b.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Bank positions in FX swaps: insights from CLS</a>
										</p>
										<p>
		</p>Authors: 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/p%c4%93teris_kloks.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Pēteris Kloks</a>, 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/patrick_mcguire.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Patrick McGuire</a>, 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/angelo_ranaldo.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Angelo Ranaldo</a> and 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/vladyslav_sushko.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Vladyslav Sushko</a>
		
										<p></p>
<p>A combination of CLS data with BIS statistics shows banks&#39; FX swaps positions alongside the currency mismatches on their balance sheets. </p>
<p><a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309b.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">More...</a></p>									
								
							
						
					
				
				
					
						
							
										
											<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309d.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
											<p></p>
											</a>
										
								
									
										<p>
												<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309d.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Unpacking international banks&#39; deposit funding</a>
										</p>
										<p>
		</p>Authors: 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/bryan_hardy.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Bryan Hardy</a> and 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/sonya_zhu.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Sonya Zhu</a>
		
										<p></p>
<p>This feature examines international banks&#39; deposit funding – traditional deposits, repos and interbank lending. We lay out a framework to interpret the observed evolution in the level and composition of this funding.  <br/></p>
<p><a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309d.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">More...</a></p>									
								
							
						
					
				
				
					
						
							
										
											<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309c.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
											<p></p>
											</a>
										
								
									
										<p>
												<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309c.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Interest rate risk management by EME banks</a>
										</p>
										<p>
		</p>Authors: 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/juli%c3%a1n_caballero.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Julián Caballero</a>, 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/alexis_maurin.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Alexis Maurin</a>, 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/philip_wooldridge.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Philip Wooldridge</a> and 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/dora_xia.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Dora Xia</a>
		
										<p></p>
<p>Banks&#39; management of interest rate risk depends on their business model as well as the environment in which they operate. <br/></p>
<p><a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309c.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">More...</a></p>									
								
							
						
					
				
				
					
						
							
										
											<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309e.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
											<p></p>
											</a>
										
								
									
										<p>
												<a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309e.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">CP and CDs markets: a primer</a>
										</p>
										<p>
		</p>Authors: 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/matteo_aquilina.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Matteo Aquilina</a>, 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/andreas_schrimpf.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Andreas Schrimpf</a> and 
				<a href="http://www.bis.org/author/karamfil_todorov.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">Karamfil Todorov</a>
		
										<p></p>
<p>Commercial paper (CP) and certificates of deposits (CDs) are important short-term funding instruments for both financial and non-financial entities. We describe the origins and evolution of these markets in major jurisdictions. <br/></p>
<p><a href="http://www.bis.org/publ/qtrpdf/r_qt2309e.htm" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">More...</a></p>									
								
							
						
					
				
	
	
